<subSubSection lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="125" pageId="17" pageNumber="124" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="17" pageNumber="124">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="125" pageId="17" pageNumber="124">
Body length 3.7 mm; ovipositor length/body length ratio = 0.64. Interantennal space with a flat triangular elevation, with a weak shallow ridge posteriorly not as elevated as the triangular elevation. Antenna with 27 flagellomeres. Third labial 
<pageBreakToken pageId="18" pageNumber="125" start="start">palpomere</pageBreakToken>
reduced, barely visible, much smaller than apical palpomere. Notauli pitted throughout. Scutellar groove with 3 longitudinal ridges. Fore tibia lacking spines; mid tibia with 6 pegs; hind tibia with 5 pegs. The Thai specimen in Figure 17 differs from the holotype in the lack of a melanic patch distally on hind femur.
</paragraph>
