<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="125" type="variation">
<paragraph pageId="18" pageNumber="125">Variation.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="18" pageNumber="125">Color usually entirely xanthic (yellow) except for brown as follows: most wing veins including stigma, antenna, hind tarsus and apex of hind tibia. Some specimens are more melanic with brown color extending to propodeum, most of hind leg and parts of most terga.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
